Bandits on Thursday afternoon invaded a Federal Government College in Birnin-Yauri, in Kebbi state and abducted scores of students.
According to an eye-witness, a policeman who tried to challenge the bandits was gunned down.
Birnin-Yauri is in Yelwa-Yauri LGA of the state.
Early in June, no fewer than 88 people were killed by bandits in communities in Danko-Wasagu Local Government Area of the State.
